==Old English==

===Etymology===
Common Germanic *''[[deuzam]]'', from Indo-European ''*dheus-''.

Germanic cognates include Old Saxon ''dior'' (Dutch ''[[dier]]''), Old High German ''[[tior]]'' (German ''[[Tier]]''), Old Norse ''[[dýr]]'' (Swedish ''[[djur]]''), Gothic [[𐌳𐌹𐌿𐍃]].  The IE root also led to Lithuanian ''dvēsti'', Lettish ''dvēsele'', Common Slavic *''[[duša]]'' (Russian [[душа]]).

